        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-3781",
        "content": "The late Samuel l Clemens (Mark Twain) advised a young man who desired to enter business to select the firm with which he wished to be associated, then ask that they give him work, without mentioning the subject of compensation.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-slow_e-normal",
